<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8">
<title>CSS Color References</title>
<style>
body {
font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
}
.name {
color: blue;
}
.hex {
color: #e67e22;
}
.rgb {
color: rgb(46, 204, 113);
}
.rgba {
color: rgba(231, 76, 60, 0.7);
}
.hsl {
color: hsl(240, 70%, 50%);
}
.hsla {
color: hsla(300, 60%, 50%, 0.8);
}
p {
font-size: 18px;

}
</style>
</head>
<body>
<h1>CSS Color Reference Examples</h1>
<p class="name">This text uses a Color Name</p>
<p class="hex">This text uses a Hexadecimal Color</p>
<p class="rgb">This text uses an RGB Color</p>
<p class="rgba">This text uses an RGBA Color</p>
<p class="hsl">This text uses an HSL Color</p>
<p class="hsla">This text uses an HSLA Color</p>
</body>
</html>
